The paper discusses the analysis of Single Event Upsets (SEUs) in SRAM-based FPGAs, which are commonly used in safety-critical applications in the aerospace industry. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Embedded Systems (cs.ET) or Architecture (cs.AR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of probabilistic model checking for reliability and safety analysis, which suggests that it may also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of mitigation techniques on design decisions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Electromagnetics (cs.EM) sub-category.
